(p = 0.009), the phase of reossification (p = 0.05) and an open triradiate 
cartilage (p = 0.0007). Our study has shown that, in the short term, VGEO 
relieves pain and corrects deformity; as growth proceeds it may produce useful 
remodelling in this worst affected subgroup of children with Perthes' disease.

