712. MMW Fortschr Med. 2000 Mar 13;142 Suppl 1:60-2.

[Chronic hepatitis C in HIV-infected patients. Unfavorable interaction of HIV 
and HCV infection].

[Article in German]

Mauss S.

HIV coinfection promotes the progression of chronic hepatitis C. The increased 
hepatic mortality and improved life expectancy of HIV-positive patients warrants 
treatment of chronic hepatitis C in those infected with HIV. The treatment of 
hepatitis C considered standard for HIV-negative and, in principle, also for 
HIV-positive patients is the combination of interferon alpha with ribavirin. 
Possible interaction with the antiretroviral treatment by ribavirin must, 
however, taken into account. Although new therapeutic approaches are available, 
they have not yet been adequately validated terms of their efficacy and safety.

